> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Plan revision:** v7 (2026-04-27) ƒ?" addresses iter-6 multi-CLI plan review. Both reviewers (Codex + Opus) converged on the same HIGH: v6 claimed the metrics-stripping fix landed at both T2 step 9 + T3 step 2 sites, but only T2 was actually patched (the v6 `replace_all` matched a string that only existed at the T2 site). T3 step 2 still had `expect(r1.bundle.ticks).toEqual(r2.bundle.ticks)` and would fail intermittently on `durationMs` timing noise. Iter-1..6 syntheses at `docs/reviews/synthetic-playtest/2026-04-27/plan-{1..6}/REVIEW.md`. v7 fixes:
